From: Hannes Reinecke <hare@kernel.org>
Date: Tue, 1 Jul 2025 16:46:57 +0200
Subject: net/handshake: Add new parameter 'HANDSHAKE_A_ACCEPT_KEYRING'
Patch-mainline: v6.17-rc1
Git-commit: e22da4685013922ade8e7b5e727ac6804fe5b51e
References: jsc#PED-16011

Add a new netlink parameter 'HANDSHAKE_A_ACCEPT_KEYRING' to provide
the serial number of the keyring to use.

Signed-off-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@kernel.org>
Reviewed-by: Chuck Lever <chuck.lever@oracle.com>
Acked-by: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20250701144657.104401-1-hare@kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Paolo Abeni <pabeni@redhat.com>
Acked-by: Pedro Falcato <pfalcato@suse.de>
---
 Documentation/netlink/specs/handshake.yaml |    4 ++++
 include/uapi/linux/handshake.h             |    1 +
 net/handshake/tlshd.c                      |    6 ++++++
 3 files changed, 11 insertions(+)

--- a/Documentation/netlink/specs/handshake.yaml
+++ b/Documentation/netlink/specs/handshake.yaml
@@ -71,6 +71,9 @@ attribute-sets:
       -
         name: peername
         type: string
+      -
+        name: keyring
+        type: u32
   -
     name: done
     attributes:
@@ -109,6 +112,7 @@ operations:
             - peer-identity
             - certificate
             - peername
+            - keyring
     -
       name: done
       doc: Handler reports handshake completion
--- a/include/uapi/linux/handshake.h
+++ b/include/uapi/linux/handshake.h
@@ -45,6 +45,7 @@ enum {
 	HANDSHAKE_A_ACCEPT_PEER_IDENTITY,
 	HANDSHAKE_A_ACCEPT_CERTIFICATE,
 	HANDSHAKE_A_ACCEPT_PEERNAME,
+	HANDSHAKE_A_ACCEPT_KEYRING,
 
 	__HANDSHAKE_A_ACCEPT_MAX,
 	HANDSHAKE_A_ACCEPT_MAX = (__HANDSHAKE_A_ACCEPT_MAX - 1)
--- a/net/handshake/tlshd.c
+++ b/net/handshake/tlshd.c
@@ -230,6 +230,12 @@ static int tls_handshake_accept(struct h
 		if (ret < 0)
 			goto out_cancel;
 	}
+	if (treq->th_keyring) {
+		ret = nla_put_u32(msg, HANDSHAKE_A_ACCEPT_KEYRING,
+				  treq->th_keyring);
+		if (ret < 0)
+			goto out_cancel;
+	}
 
 	ret = nla_put_u32(msg, HANDSHAKE_A_ACCEPT_AUTH_MODE,
 			  treq->th_auth_mode);
